By Hussaini Hammangabdo, The former Acting Governor of Adamawa State, James Barka, has dumped the All Progressive Congress (APC), to the ruling People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in the state. Barka who defected alongside with many others decampees said his decision followed wide consultation and carefully studied the feat recorded by the present leadership in the state. He said that he was attracted back to the PDP based on unprecedented developmental projects by Governor Ahmadu Fintiri within last one year in office. “I’ve always been a PDP man. Under their party I was elected member of the state Assembly and I became the Speaker. “Under the same PDP I became acting governor and later ambassador. “I only veered off into the APC, leaving my teeming supporters behind. “I’ve returned home. I am impressed with Fintiri achievement within short time”, he added. Governor Ahmadu Fintiri who received the former speaker, said the door of PDP is wide open to accommodate all progressive minded people who want to join him in moving the state forward. He added that his administration will continue with people oriented projects. Hamza Madagali PDP Organising Secretary in the state said that, Fintiri’s achievement will continue to be the winning card of the PDP in any election. He commended Barka James for taking a bold step and return to the PDP family. Madagali assured that, Fintiri remain consistent with his  agenda of developing the state. 